{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778468397545,"sessionID":"ses_1eb09b109ffeoer5llC2d0y8Fw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:32","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ## Summary\n2: \n3: Added the missing `part_of` relationship between **GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly** and **GO:0072583 clathrin-dependent endocytosis**, plus a `term_tracker_item` linking back to issue #31981.\n4: \n5: ### Why `part_of` and not `is_a`\n6: \n7: The original issue title suggested adding a missing \"parent\", which typically implies an `is_a` link. However, @pgaudet correctly noted that this should be `part_of`. Clathrin coat disassembly is a discrete step *within* clathrin-dependent endocytosis (it strips the clathrin coat from clathrin-coated vesicles before they fuse with their targets), not a subtype of endocytosis itself. This is also consistent with the existing axiom on the parent term **GO:0072319 vesicle uncoating**, which is `part_of` **GO:0016192 vesicle-mediated transport**.\n8: \n9: ### Changes made\n10: \n11: - **File edited:** `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n12: - **Term affected:** `GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly`\n13: - **Added:**\n14:   - `relationship: part_of GO:0072583 ! clathrin-dependent endocytosis`\n15:   - `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31981\" xsd:anyURI`\n16: \n17: ### Checklist\n18: \n19: - [x] Issue intent analyzed and clear\n20: - [x] Relevant terms looked up in current ontology\n21: - [x] Relationship type (`part_of`) chosen based on biological context and existing patterns\n22: - [x] Term edited using checkout/checkin procedure (`obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl`)\n23: - [x] SPARQL-QC checks passed\n24: - [x] ELK reasoning passed with no unsatisfiable classes\n25: - [x] Only edited file committed (`src/ontology/go-edit.obo`)\n\n(End of file - total 25 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Summary\n\nAdded the missing `part_of` relationship between **GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly** and **GO:0072583 clathrin-dependent endocytosis**, plus a `term_tracker_item` linking back to issue #31981.\n\n### Why `part_of` and not `is_a`\n\nThe original issue title suggested adding a missing \"parent\", which typically implies an `is_a` link. However, @pgaudet correctly noted that this should be `part_of`. Clathrin coat disassembly is a discrete step *within* clathrin-dependent endocytosis (it strips the clathrin coat from clathrin-coated vesicles before they fuse with their targets), not a subtype of endocytosis itself. This is also consistent with the existing axiom on the parent term **GO:0072319 vesicle uncoating**, which is `part_of` **GO:0016192 vesicle-mediated transport**.\n\n### Changes made\n\n- **File edited:** `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n- **Term affected:** `GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly`\n- **Added:**\n  - `relationship: part_of GO:0072583 ! clathrin-dependent endocytosis`\n  - `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31981\" xsd:anyURI`\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] Issue intent analyzed and clear\n- [x] Relevant terms looked up in current ontology","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778468397538,"end":1778468397544}},"id":"prt_e14fa21e0001BpuB5KpGZ17qhE","sessionID":"ses_1eb09b109ffeoer5llC2d0y8Fw","messageID":"msg_e14fa073a001vqd0nuxyxk5gKI"}}
