{"type":"text","timestamp":1778468401157,"sessionID":"ses_1eb09b109ffeoer5llC2d0y8Fw","part":{"id":"prt_e14fa2aad002o59aA91d2LQk3h","messageID":"msg_e14fa222b001DWTztZBukLxguI","sessionID":"ses_1eb09b109ffeoer5llC2d0y8Fw","type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what I did:\n\n### Changes made\n- **File edited:** `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n- Added `relationship: part_of GO:0072583 ! clathrin-dependent endocytosis` to **GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly**\n- Added `property_value: term_tracker_item` linking back to issue #31981\n- Committed locally (did **not** push)\n\n### Rationale for `part_of` instead of `is_a`\nThe original issue suggested adding a missing \"parent\". However, @pgaudet correctly noted that `part_of` is the appropriate relationship here. Clathrin coat disassembly is a step *within* clathrin-dependent endocytosis, not a subtype of it. This is also consistent with the pattern on **GO:0072319 vesicle uncoating**, which is `part_of` **GO:0016192 vesicle-mediated transport**.\n\n### Validation\n- SPARQL-QC checks: **all passed** (0 violations)\n- ELK reasoning: **passed** with no unsatisfiable classes\n\n### Files created\n- `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md` — brief update for the originating issue\n- `PR_COMMENTS.md` — detailed PR description with rationale and checklist\n\nNeither markdown file was committed, as requested.","time":{"start":1778468399789,"end":1778468401155}}}
